								<p class="small muted">Sunday, September  6, 2020</p>
								
								
	
								<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef026bde90154f200c"></a>
							
								
								<h3><a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html"><strong><em>Two Professors Sue Florida Coastal Law School For Breach Of Contract Over Pay Cut</em></strong></a></h3>
								
								
								<div class="line">
									<p class="author"> By <a href="#">Paul Caron</a></p>
									
									<div class="share hidden-phone">
										<a href="#"><i class="icon-share"></i> Share</a>
										<div class="dropdown clearfix">
											<div class="tab-arrow"></div>
											<ul class="clearfix">
												<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html"><i class="icon-facebook"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html&text=<strong><em>Two Professors Sue Florida Coastal Law School For Breach Of Contract Over Pay Cut</em></strong>&via=SoCalTaxProf"><i class="icon-twitter"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html"><i class="icon-google-plus"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html"><i class="icon-linkedin"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="mailto:?subject=<strong><em>Two Professors Sue Florida Coastal Law School For Breach Of Contract Over Pay Cut</em></strong> on The Taxprof Blog&body=Check this article out on The Taxprof Blog: https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html"><i class="icon-envelope"></i></a></li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
	
								</div>
	
								<div class="hidden-phone">
	
									<p>News4Jax, <a href="https://www.news4jax.com/news/local/2020/09/03/professors-sue-florida-coastal-school-of-law-over-breach-of-contract/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Professors Sue Florida Coastal School of Law Over ‘Breach of Contract’</a>:</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><a class="asset-img-link" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40ee134200d-popup" onclick="window.open( this.href, &#39;_blank&#39;, &#39;width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0&#39; ); return false" style="float: right;"><img alt="Florida Coastal (2017)" class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40ee134200d img-responsive" src="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40ee134200d-300wi" style="width: 300px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="Florida Coastal (2017)" /></a>Two law professors are suing Florida Coastal School of Law in a complaint that accuses the for-profit school’s owners of putting their own interests ahead of the school’s.</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">The four-count lawsuit was filed July 17 in Duval County by the law firm of Morgan &amp; Morgan on behalf of law professors <a href="https://www.fcsl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/BJ-Priester.pdf" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Benjamin Priester</a> and <a href="https://www.fcsl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Jennifer-Reiber.pdf" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Jennifer Reiber</a>. The professors, who have taught at the school for over a decade each, are seeking more than $30,000 in damages and a jury trial.</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">Among other things, the suit accuses Florida Coastal School of Law and its ownership of breach of contract by unilaterally cutting employees’ agreed upon salaries to offset budget shortfalls. It says the professors, who would not have kept working for the school if their pay wasn’t misrepresented, are owed unpaid wages.</p>

									
									<p><a class="btn btn-small" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/two-professors-sue-florida-coastal-law-school-for-breach-of-contract-over-pay-cut.html#more">Continue reading <i class="icon-double-angle-right"></i></a></p>
	
									
									
