							<div class="article" style="border-bottom: 5px solid #00205c;">
								
								
								
	
								<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40ea443200d"></a>
							
								
								<h3><a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html"><strong><em>Jobs Report: U.S. Economy Adds 1.4 Million Jobs, Legal Profession Adds ... Nothing</em></strong></a></h3>
								
								
								<div class="line">
									<p class="author"> By <a href="#">Paul Caron</a></p>
									
									<div class="share hidden-phone">
										<a href="#"><i class="icon-share"></i> Share</a>
										<div class="dropdown clearfix">
											<div class="tab-arrow"></div>
											<ul class="clearfix">
												<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html"><i class="icon-facebook"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html&text=<strong><em>Jobs Report: U.S. Economy Adds 1.4 Million Jobs, Legal Profession Adds ... Nothing</em></strong>&via=SoCalTaxProf"><i class="icon-twitter"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html"><i class="icon-google-plus"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html"><i class="icon-linkedin"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="mailto:?subject=<strong><em>Jobs Report: U.S. Economy Adds 1.4 Million Jobs, Legal Profession Adds ... Nothing</em></strong> on The Taxprof Blog&body=Check this article out on The Taxprof Blog: https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html"><i class="icon-envelope"></i></a></li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
	
								</div>
	
								<div class="hidden-phone">
	
									<p style="text-align: justify;">American Lawyer, <a href="https://www.law.com/2020/09/04/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-1-4-million-jobs-legal-adds-nothing/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Jobs Report: US Economy Adds 1.4 Million Jobs, Legal Adds ... Nothing</a>:</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><a class="asset-img-link" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40e8b84200d-popup" onclick="window.open( this.href, &#39;_blank&#39;, &#39;width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0&#39; ); return false" style="float: right;"><img alt="BLS (2015)" class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40e8b84200d img-responsive" src="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40e8b84200d-250wi" style="width: 225px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="BLS (2015)" /></a>Zero. Zip. Zilch. Nada. While the U.S. economy overall added 1.4 million jobs in August, buoyed by almost 250,000 temporary census workers that will be laid off at month’s end, the legal vertical added exactly zero jobs, according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics’&#0160;<a href="https://www.bls.gov/news.release/empsit.nr0.htm" rel="noopener" target="_blank">monthly jobs report</a>.&#0160;</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">While not counted in this month’s report, a&#0160;<a href="https://www.law.com/americanlawyer/2020/09/03/nixon-peabody-makes-another-round-of-layoffs-while-restoring-some-staff-pay/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">spat of layoffs</a>&#0160;in recent days suggests that a flat month of job growth might be the best the industry can expect for some time.&#0160;</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">The number of jobs in the legal sector, composed of attorneys, paralegals, legal secretaries and others who make their living in the law, sat at 1,107,600, the same number as July and about 45,000 jobs lower than the same point in 2019.&#0160;</p>

									
									<p><a class="btn btn-small" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/jobs-report-us-economy-adds-14-million-jobs-legal-profession-adds-nothing.html#more">Continue reading <i class="icon-double-angle-right"></i></a></p>
	
									
									
