							<div class="article" style="border-bottom: 5px solid #00205c;">
								
								
								
	
								<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef026bde8f3868200c"></a>
							
								
								<h3><a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html"><strong><em>California Bar Posts Draft Rules For Provisional Licensing Program</em></strong></a></h3>
								
								
								<div class="line">
									<p class="author"> By <a href="#">Paul Caron</a></p>
									
									<div class="share hidden-phone">
										<a href="#"><i class="icon-share"></i> Share</a>
										<div class="dropdown clearfix">
											<div class="tab-arrow"></div>
											<ul class="clearfix">
												<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html"><i class="icon-facebook"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html&text=<strong><em>California Bar Posts Draft Rules For Provisional Licensing Program</em></strong>&via=SoCalTaxProf"><i class="icon-twitter"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html"><i class="icon-google-plus"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html"><i class="icon-linkedin"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="mailto:?subject=<strong><em>California Bar Posts Draft Rules For Provisional Licensing Program</em></strong> on The Taxprof Blog&body=Check this article out on The Taxprof Blog: https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html"><i class="icon-envelope"></i></a></li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
	
								</div>
	
								<div class="hidden-phone">
	
									<p>The Recorder, <a href="https://www.law.com/therecorder/2020/09/02/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">State Bar Posts Draft Rules for Provisional Licensing Program</a>:</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><a class="asset-img-link" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40e03f6200d-popup" onclick="window.open( this.href, &#39;_blank&#39;, &#39;width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0&#39; ); return false" style="float: right;"><img alt="California Bar Exam" class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40e03f6200d img-responsive" src="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40e03f6200d-250wi" style="width: 216px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="California Bar Exam" /></a>California’s state bar is asking for <a href="http://www.calbar.ca.gov/About-Us/Our-Mission/Protecting-the-Public/Public-Comment/Public-Comment-Archives/2020-Public-Comment/New-Provisional-Licensure-Rule-Rule-of-Court-XX" rel="noopener" target="_blank">public comments</a>&#0160;on a proposed provisional licensing program that will allow recent law school graduates to practice law temporarily without taking the bar exam.</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">A six-page draft&#0160;<a href="http://www.calbar.ca.gov/Portals/0/documents/publicComment/2020/Draft-Provisional-Licensure-Rule-of-Court-for-Circulation-for-Public-Comment.pdf" rel="noopener" target="_blank">rule of court</a>&#0160;spells out what the program will require.</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><strong>&gt;&gt;</strong>&#0160;Anyone who became eligible, or will become eligible, to sit for a bar exam between Dec. 1, 2019, and Dec. 31, 2020, can apply for provisional licensing.</p>

									
									<p><a class="btn btn-small" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/09/state-bar-posts-draft-rules-for-provisional-licensing-program.html#more">Continue reading <i class="icon-double-angle-right"></i></a></p>
	
									
									
