								<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef026be40cdaa6200d"></a>
							
								
								<h3><a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html"><strong><em>Washburn Law School Removes Statues Of Ben Franklin, Thomas Jefferson</em></strong></a></h3>
								
								
								<div class="line">
									<p class="author"> By <a href="#">Paul Caron</a></p>
									
									<div class="share hidden-phone">
										<a href="#"><i class="icon-share"></i> Share</a>
										<div class="dropdown clearfix">
											<div class="tab-arrow"></div>
											<ul class="clearfix">
												<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html"><i class="icon-facebook"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html&text=<strong><em>Washburn Law School Removes Statues Of Ben Franklin, Thomas Jefferson</em></strong>&via=SoCalTaxProf"><i class="icon-twitter"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html"><i class="icon-google-plus"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html"><i class="icon-linkedin"></i></a></li>
												<li><a href="mailto:?subject=<strong><em>Washburn Law School Removes Statues Of Ben Franklin, Thomas Jefferson</em></strong> on The Taxprof Blog&body=Check this article out on The Taxprof Blog: https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html"><i class="icon-envelope"></i></a></li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
	
								</div>
	
								<div class="hidden-phone">
	
									<p><a class="asset-img-link" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026bde8e0ae7200c-popup" onclick="window.open( this.href, &#39;_blank&#39;, &#39;width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0&#39; ); return false"><img alt="Franklin" border="0" class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef026bde8e0ae7200c image-full img-responsive" src="https://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef026bde8e0ae7200c-800wi" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" title="Franklin" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">U.S. News &amp; World Report, <a href="https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/missouri/articles/2020-08-27/washburn-university-removed-jefferson-franklin-statues" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Statues Of Jefferson, Franklin Removed From Washburn Campus</a>:</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">Statues of Thomas Jefferson and Benjamin Franklin have been removed from the Washburn University campus after protests against racial injustice elsewhere led to statues honoring slaveholders being vandalized, pulled down or moved, the school said Thursday.</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">The two bronze statues that had stood outside the university&#39;s law school in Topeka for two decades were removed in July after Washburn President Jerry Farley discussed the concerns with the family of the donor, who has since died, school spokesman Patrick Early said. ...</p>
<p style="margin: 15px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px none; outline: 0px none; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: #ebf0f3; line-height: 20px; color: #363636; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">Some Washburn students have questioned the propriety of the statutes but the decision to remove them from campus was not in response to a protest or request from students, Early said.&#0160;“It was the donor&#39;s decision to have the statues returned,&quot; he said. “They didn&#39;t want the statues to become a source of embarrassment so they asked that they be returned.&quot;</p>

									
									<p><a class="btn btn-small" href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html#more">Continue reading <i class="icon-double-angle-right"></i></a></p>
	
									
									
									<p class="posted">
									August 31, 2020 in <a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/legal-ed-news/">Legal Ed News</a>, <a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/legal-education/">Legal Education</a>  | <a href="https://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2020/08/washburn-law-school-removes-statues-of-ben-franklin-thomas-jefferson.html">Permalink</a>
									
